import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    for industry in data['series'].unique():
        industry_data = data[data['series'] == industry]
        plt.plot(industry_data['date'], industry_data['rate'], label=industry)
    
    plt.title("What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Unemployment Rate")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Industry", loc="upper left")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    specific_year = 2009  # Change this value to the desired year
    data = data[data['year'] == specific_year]
    
    data = data.groupby('series')['rate'].max().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values('rate', ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(data['series'], data['rate'], color=plt.cm.Paired.colors)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.xlabel('Industry')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title(f'Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in {specific_year}?', wrap=True)
    
    max_rate = data['rate'].max()
    max_industry = data.loc[data['rate'] == max_rate, 'series'].values[0]
    plt.axhline(max_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Rate: {max_industry} ({max_rate:.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    industries = data['series'].unique()
    colors = plt.cm.tab20(range(len(industries)))
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    for i, industry in enumerate(industries):
        industry_data = data[data['series'] == industry]
        plt.hist(industry_data['count'], bins=30, alpha=0.5, color=colors[i], label=industry)
    
    plt.xlabel('Number of Unemployed Individuals')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployed individuals across all industries?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Industry', loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['count'], data['rate'], c=data['series'].astype('category').cat.codes, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Industries")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    plt.xlabel('Number of Unemployed Individuals')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of unemployed individuals and the unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
